instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Model fidelity is ensured through cross‑validation, where simulated temperature trajectories are statistically compared to experimental data collected during controlled incubator runs; an RMSE threshold of 1 °C defines acceptable fidelity. Verification is conducted via unit tests for each differential equation, ensuring dimensional consistency, and simulation‐based sanity checks. Uncertainty quantification employs Monte‑Carlo propagation of sensor noise (±0.5 °C) and parameter variability, yielding confidence intervals for predicted temperatures. Error detection includes real‑time outlier detection by comparing sensor readings to the model’s Kalman filter predictions; deviations beyond 3σ trigger fault alerts. Quality assurance processes involve version‑controlled storage of CAD, simulation and control scripts in a git repository with audit trails, and periodic review of calibration datasets to confirm residual error minimization."
]
